  "text": "Proteins were expressed in XL1-blue Escherichia coli (Stratagene), grown in Luria Broth supplemented with 100 mM ZnCl 2 [CITATION_1] . They were purified by Talon Õ chromatography as described [CITATION_2] . Minor contaminants were removed and proteins were transferred into storage buffer (20 mM Tris (pH 8.0 at 20 C), 250 mM NaCl, 1 mM DTT (dithiothreitol)) by chromatography on Sephadex G-50. Protein solutions were stored frozen at À80 C until needed. AGT concentrations were measured spectrophotometrically using e 280 = 3.93 Â 10 4 M À1 cm À1 [CITATION_3] . The samples of AGT used here were >95% active in DNA binding [CITATION_4] .",
